CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper February 20, 1965, pg. 14, reads: "Booze Personified - The Teen Team Orators added zest to their Sunday night presentation with dramatic impersonations. Here Lillie Mae Nelson (left) plays the part of 'King Alcohol' and tries, without success, to entice Roce [Rose] Lee Jackson, representative of thousands of innocent youth. 'I'm the Greatest!' King Alcohol exclaimed. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Lillie Mae Nelson in paper costume acting as "King Alcohol" with Rose Lee Jackson seated beside her, in John Wesley AME Zion church
